custom_nodes.author: ecjojo
custom_nodes.title: ecjojo_example_nodes
custom_nodes.description:
Welcome to ecjojo_example_nodes! This example is specifically designed for beginners who want to learn how to write a simple custom node.
Feel free to modify this example and make it your own. Experiment with different features and functionalities to enhance your understanding of Hanzo Studio custom nodes. Don't be afraid to explore and customize the code to suit your needs.
By diving into this example and making it your own, you'll gain valuable hands-on experience in creating custom nodes in Hanzo Studio. Enjoy the process of learning and have fun with your custom node development journey!

custom_nodes.author: andrewharp
custom_nodes.title: Hanzo Studio Function Annotator
custom_nodes.description: This module provides an annotation @ComfyFunc to streamline adding custom node types in Hanzo Studio. It processes your function's signature to create a wrapped function and custom node definition required for Hanzo Studio, eliminating all the boilerplate code. In most cases you can just add a @ComfyFunc("category") annotation to your existing function.
